The '''critique of ideology''' is a concept in [[critical theory]]. It [[logical consequence|entails]] the submission of received understanding to critical reappropriation for the purpose of human emancipation.<ref>See the Stanford Encyclopedia of Philosophy, [http://plato.stanford.edu/entries/critical-theory/ Critical Theory], for examples of usage.</ref> An important part of [[ideology]] critique has to do with “looking suspiciously at works of art and debunking them as tools of oppression.”<ref>Rita Felski (2004) “The Role of Aesthetics in Cultural Studies” in ''The Aesthetics of Cultural Studies'' (ed. Michael Bérubé). Malden, MA: Blackwell, p. 30</ref>
